{
  "message": "fix: bd init falls back to JSONL mode when CGO unavailable (dolt-ea0sh)\n\nWindows CI builds with CGO_ENABLED=0, so the Dolt backend is unavailable.\nPreviously bd init would fail with \"dolt backend requires CGO\". Now it\ndetects the CGO error and falls back to --no-db (JSONL-only) mode\nautomatically, enabling the full CRUD smoke test to pass.\n\nAlso fixes a copy-paste bug at init.go:355 where the else branch\nhardcoded configfile.BackendDolt instead of using the backend variable.\n\nAdds missing //go:build cgo tags to 26 test files that reference\nCGO-only types/helpers, preventing compilation failures on nocgo builds.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
